Python script that allows to move electrodes.
**********************************************

Usage : python move_electrodes.py *value* 
Value is what you want to add or take off on each side.
**********************************************
examples : 
	python move_electrodes.py -1 --> will take off 1 a.u. to the left side and 1 a.u. to the right side.
	python move_electrodes.py +2 --> will add 2 a.u. to both the left and the right side.
**********************************************

You only need one file that is data.inpt, containing only the header and the coordinates (no velocities etc..)
It works only for planar electrodes. 
